headline: Packaging Corp.: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The results fell short of Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of five analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $2.51 per share. The maker of containerboard and corrugated packaging products posted revenue of $2.15 billion in the period, exceeding Street forecasts.
